definition:
&%SantaAnaWinds are strong, extremely dry 
&%KatabaticWind winds that originate from cool, dry high-pressure air masses in the &%GreatBasin.
They arise in higher altitudes and blowing down towards sea level. The National Weather 
Service defines Santa Ana winds as a weather condition in southern California in which strong, 
hot, dust-bearing winds descend to the Pacific Coast around Los Angeles from inland desert regions.
[Wikipedia]
